This paper is about the computational methods for solving the electrostatic interactions between biological molecules in solution. It involves algorithmic and hardware acceleration, which are common topics in the computer science sub-categories of computational engineering (cs.CE), numerical analysis (cs.NA), modeling and simulation (cs.MS), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), and scientific computing (cs.SC).
